# WordPress Theme and Plugin Development Guidelines

## Theme Development
When working in [wordpress/wp-content/themes/](mdc:wordpress/wp-content/themes/):
- New themes need at minimum `style.css` (with theme header) and `index.php`
- Follow WordPress coding standards for PHP
- Use proper WordPress hooks and filters
- Enqueue scripts and styles properly using `wp_enqueue_script()` and `wp_enqueue_style()`

## Plugin Development  
When working in [wordpress/wp-content/plugins/](mdc:wordpress/wp-content/plugins/):
- Include proper plugin headers in main PHP file
- Use WordPress hooks (`add_action`, `add_filter`) for functionality
- Follow WordPress security best practices (nonces, sanitization, validation)
- Use WordPress database functions (`$wpdb`, `get_option`, etc.)

## WordPress Best Practices
- Always escape output using `esc_html()`, `esc_attr()`, `esc_url()`
- Sanitize input data
- Use WordPress conditional tags (`is_home()`, `is_single()`, etc.)
- Leverage WordPress template hierarchy
- Use WordPress coding standards for naming (underscores, not camelCase for functions/variables)